f ad hoc requests  FERPA compliance  continued development of technology and post wide availability of data to the community  The Registrar s Office meets its mission through  Seeking ways to continually improve the level of service to the user community  This is accomplished through a continual review of technological capabilities  and the development of supporting processes and procedures that will enhance information accessibility to cadets  faculty and administrative personnel  Upholding quality standards and ensuring that the integrity  accuracy and security of data remains at exceptional quality  Real time processing of information to provide the post community direct access to the most up to date and accurate information available  To support the end users to be more self sufficient within the decentralized structure  Promoting personal  courteous and cooperative customer service in meeting the needs of the user community  To serve the cadets  parents  faculty  alumni  staff and general public within the parameters established by law  Suggest a Link  If there is a page from the VMI website that you use frequently and would like added to the Registrar s Office webpage  please let us know Click here to suggest a link  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 